author: Jim Kleinpeter, NOLA.com | The Times-Picayune
title: LSU vs. Florida to kickoff at 6 p.m. CT on ESPN
text:
LSU and Florida will kick off at 6 p.m. CT Oct. 17 on ESPN, the SEC announced Monday. CBS picked the Alabama-Texas A&M game for the 2:30 time slot.
It's the second night game in Tiger Stadium this season. LSU has had three daytime kickoffs in the first five weeks, including this Saturday's 11 a.m. start at South Carolina.
Auburn will be at Kentucky at 6 p.m. CT on ESPN on Thursday, Oct. 15 to start the week.
The rest of the SEC lineup has Ole Miss at Memphis at 11 a.m. CT; Louisiana Tech at Mississippi State at 11 a.m. on the SEC Network; Vanderbilt at South Carolina at 3 p.m. on the SEC Network; and Missouri at Georgia, 6:30 p.m. SEC Network. All times are central
